    <p>OCT 20, 1976</p>
    <p>Made his de­but in Ar­gentina’s top flight for Buenos Aires side Ar­genti­nos Ju­niors, just be­fore his 16th birth­day. He went on to win his first cap for Ar­gentina in Feb 27, 1977. His first goal for Ar­gentina came in a 3-1 win over Scot­land at Ham­p­den Park in Glas­gow in 1979.</p>
    <p>JUNE 13, 1982</p>
    <p>Now a Boca Ju­niors player, Maradona com­peted in a World Cup match for the first time as the hold­ers lost 1-0 to Bel­gium in Spain. What was most mem­o­rable about that game was the iconic pho­to­graph of six Bel­gian play­ers con­fronting him – a tes­ta­ment to his rep­u­ta­tion.</p>
    <p>JULY 5, 1984</p>
    <p>Napoli pulled off a coup to sign Maradona for a then world-record fee of £6.9 mil­lion (S$12.3 mil­lion). He in­spired the club to Serie A suc­cesses in 1987 and 1990 as well as the Uefa Cup in 1989.</p>

